commit.message:
Added dedicated fields for API keys in settings file

API endpoints are also being changed.

Added MP4 support

Since we're using ffmpeg, added "mp4" to the list of supported
extensions (note that this might not work if ffmpeg doesn't recognize
the codec used). Thanks to Maxwell Gibbard for the prompt.

Fixed a typo

Previously said "IMG_206 is Scene 1"; this information alone would not be enough to determine the labels of IMG_201 through IMG_205, as the scene letter might have changed. This is a problem in the documentation; the code in the interpolator shouldn't need to be currently changed, I think.
Added status updates; move_and_org now adds numbers.

Updated README and cleaned repository

Removing everything other than corpus and New GUI.

Drag-and-drop behavior now checks if code's running.

when it needs to be disabled.

Previously, the destination variable (which we look up in the
BackgroundWorker) wasn't being set when the settings file was being
loaded.
Setting it there fixed it.
